5000|$|The Center for the Study of Democratic Institutions in Santa Barbara, California was an {{influential}} think tank from 1959 to 1977. Its influence waned thereafter and it closed in 1987. It held discussions on subjects it hoped would influence <b>public</b> <b>deliberation.</b> It attained some controversy with its conference of student radical leaders in 1967, {{and with a}} suggested new U.S. Constitution proposed by Fellow Rexford G. Tugwell.|$|E
